11:44 Halee Garrison appears with attorney Craker.  Peter Kruger appears on behalf of the state.
Court reviews file; quashes warrant and requests current address.  Defendant indicates that her address is 7970 Franklin Street.  Court informs defendant that whoever lives at that address has contacted clerk of courts and that is not her address.  Defendant does not have an address. Attorney Craker indicates General Delivery, Superior WI.
Attorney Craker indicates had 2 rides fall through this morning and was attempting to walk.  She got in touch with pastor Jack who brought her to court.  She was coming from the Itasca area.
Court questions why defendant is appearing now, hearing was at 9:45 and why it took two hours to get here.
Defendant indicates Uber and lift were unavailable, cabs crashed and started to walk.
State indicates she has posted 750cb, was out on a sb on previous file and there has been 2 other fta's.
State not opposed to cash being reinstated but requests and additional $50 cash be posted. Appreciates that Pastor Jack helped her.
Court has concerns, has prior failures to appear, has failures to appear in Minnesota. Has concerns about the address that she gave today and not being able to give an address to the court.  When questioned about where she was this morning, couldn't give a definite place-just the Itasca area.
Attorney Craker indicates this is her situation; couch surfing.  Going to start treatment at Lake Superior Treatment Center today.
Court questions ability to post $50cb/
Defendant does not know if she will be able to post.  Might have $25 in her account.
Court will not issue any additional cash.  Completely understands State's request for additional $50.
Court sets for preliminary hearing; can go outside of time limits because of non appearance. Sets prelim for 4/13/22 11am
